OL,7,FEarlier Dr Mark Ainsley, clinical
OL,8,Fdirector of cardiology for the
OL,9,Fhospital trust, said if Mr Gibson's
OL,10,Fheart problem had been spotted on the
OL,11,FECG scan he would possibly have been
OL,12,Fmonitored and treated there and then
OL,13,Fand fitted with a pacemaker, a
OL,14,Fprocedure that takes "less than an
OL,15,Fhour", he said.
OL,17,FThe coroner asked: "Do you think that
OL,18,Fsequence of events would likely have
OL,19,Favoided his death?"
OL,26,@vD@VOUwD@EO]yD@TOU{D@SO]
